Carta Roberti cobbe de trib denariis in Oystañ.
m̃ib xp̃i ⁊c̃ Rob̃tus Cobbe de Brokesheued sal̃tm Nou̾it uniu̾sitas ur̃a me dedisse ⁊ concessisse ⁊ p̾sen
ti carta mea cofirmasse deo ⁊ beate marie ⁊ domu frm̃ hospital̃ sc̃i Ioh̃is ieros̃ in uilla de Chaur̃ ꝓ salute aĩe mee
⁊ ancessoꝵ ⁊ successoꝵ meoꝵ tres denar̃ quos Ranulfus Capellanꝰ de Eystañ mͥ annuatim reddere cõsueuit cũ homa
gio ⁊ seruic̃ ip̃ius h̃end̃ ⁊ tenẽd̃ de me ⁊ heredib meis dc̃is ffr̾ib hospit̃ ⁊ eoꝵ successorib in lib̃am ⁊ purã ⁊ ꝑpetuã
elemosinã ita lib̃e ⁊ pure sicuti elemosina lib̃ius ⁊ purius pt̃ dari uel recipi Ego uero Rob̃tus ⁊ hered̃ mei waranti-
zabimꝰ p̾dc̃am donũ p̾dc̃is fratrib⁊ eoꝵ successorib sicuti nr̃am lib̃am puram ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinam contͣ om̃es
hom̃ies ⁊ fem̃ias Et ut h̃ mea donacio ⁊ cõcessio ⁊ carte mee confirmacio ⁊ warãtizacio rate ⁊ stabiles imꝑp̃m
ꝑseuerẽt p̾sens scriptũ sigilli mei appõne roboraui hiis testib | ⁊c̃
Carta Constancie filie Rc̃i Ailberne n de uii. acris terre
m̃ib xp̃i ⁊c̃ Constancia filia Rc̃i Aylb̃n de Brokesheued sal̃tm in dño Nou̾it̃ me ꝓ salute aĩe mee ⁊
om̃i p̾decessoꝵ ⁊ successoꝵ meoꝵ dedisse ⁊ quiet̃ clamasse ⁊ hac p̾senti carta mea confirmasse deo ⁊ beate marie
⁊ sc̃o Ioh̃i Bap̃te ⁊ beatis pauꝑib sc̃e domꝰ hospit̃ irl̃m in Angl̃ ⁊ fratrib eiusdem domꝰ deo seruienc̃ ⁊ apud
chaur̃ cõmorãtib in lib̃am purã ⁊ ꝑpetuam elemosinã septem acras t̾re arabl̃es cũ suis ꝑtĩn q̃ iacent in cãpo
qͥ vocat᷑ Beschton int̾ t̾ram walt̾i heruy ⁊ t̾ram henrici clarice ⁊ abbutat unũ capud suꝑ t̾ram dñi de Brokes
heued ⁊ aliud capud suꝑ regale cheminũ h̃end̃ ⁊ tenẽd̃ p̾dc̃e domui ⁊ frĩb lib̃e ⁊ quiet̃ b̃n ⁊ in pace ⁊ absq om̃ib
exacciõib secl̃ar̃ sic̃ aliqua elemosina lib̃ius ⁊ quiecius dari p̃t alcͥ domui religionis Et ego p̾dc̃a constancia ⁊
hered̃ mei warantizabimꝰ ⁊ defendemꝰ p̾dc̃am t̾ram cũ ꝑtĩn suis p̾dc̃e domui ⁊ frĩb apud chaur̃ cõmorãtib
sic̃ p̾dc̃m est contͣ om̃es gẽtes imꝑp̃m In huiꝰ rei testimoniũ p̾senti carte sigill̃ũ meũ apposui Hiis testib ⁊c̃.
Carta Godwini Seregot ⁊ ux̃ sue de eisdm̃ uii acris
mĩb xp̃i ⁊c̃ Godewinus Seregot ⁊ Maltida uxor mea sal̃t̃m in dño  ͩSciatis remisimꝰ ⁊ ⁊ quiet̃ clamauimꝰ deo ⁊
beate marie ⁊ sc̃o Ioh̃m Bap̃te ⁊ beatis pauꝑib domus hospit̃ irl̃m in angl̃ ⁊ fr̾ib eiusdem domꝰ deo seruienc̃
apud Chaur̃ totũ ius ⁊ clameũ qd̶ h̃uimꝰ uel h̃ere potuimꝰ in tota dote q̃ nos cõtingit de uii acris t̾re arabil̃ cũ
ꝑtĩn q̃ fuerũt aliqũ Rc̃i Ailberñ ⁊ iacent in campo qͥ vocat᷑ Beschtoñ Et ne de cet̾o aliquid uendicare possimꝰ
huic scripto sigilla nr̃a apposuimꝰ hiis testib dño Rc̃o Giffard̃ ⁊ aliis ⁊c̃.
.Carta predc̃e constancie de una acia t̾re in chaureth̃
m̃ib xp̃i ⁊c̃ Constancia filia Rc̃i ayl̃b̃n de Brokesheued sal̃tm in dño Nou̾it̃ me dedisse concessisse ⁊ hac
p̾senti carta mea confirmasse deo ⁊ beate marie ⁊ sc̃o Ioh̃m ⁊ pauꝑib irl̃m ⁊ domui de chaur̃ in purã ⁊ ꝑpetuã
elemosinam unam acram t̾re mee cũ ꝑtĩn in ꝑochia de Chaur̃ q̃ iacet int̃ t̾ram Ioh̃is Oteberd ⁊ t̾ram meã
unde unũ capud abuttat suꝑ mariscũ luc̃ de Brokesheued ⁊ aliud capud suꝑ Bradecroft Broc In cuiꝰ rei testĩo-
niũ huic p̾senti scripto ⁊c̃ hiis testib ⁊c̃.
